##7. Scope limits
We will not estimate structural causal drivers of default (e.g., how macroeconomic shocks impact default rates).
We are modeling Probability of Default (PD) only; we will not estimate Loss Given Default (LGD) or Exposure at Default (EAD).
We will drop variables that reflect post-default outcomes (e.g., collections, recoveries) as they introduce target leakage.
We will not deploy the model as a live, consumer-facing API or web application.


##8. Risks and fallback
Risk: The automated Weight of Evidence (WoE) binning algorithm fails to find logical, monotonic relationships for highly predictive but non-linear continuous variables, causing a massive drop in scorecard performance.
Fallback: We will manually enforce equal-frequency decile binning for problematic variables and group them using business domain logic, or fall back to spline-transformed logistic regression to capture non-linearities while retaining additive interpretability.


